snippet.textDisplay:
Besides all the goals Haaland scroes, did you guys see the run he made after heading a ball from a corner in front of his own goal? It litterally took seconds and he came in high speed on the other half and had a free line to the goal if he would have received the ball.. Sancho should have passed to him 2 or 3 times when he had postitionied himself with a free space in front of him. He could have scored 5 that game if he got the ball.

I think Sancho sometimes dont want to play him cause I think he is a bit «jealous» that Haaland gets so much praise when he was the one getting the most praise before he came. Well, its understandable in a way cause Sancho is a really good player, with so much skills, but sometimes he does the wrong choices and he rather tries to do something himself instead of passing to Haaland or he makes a pass that slows up the game. Some of you may think Haaland scores easy tap in goals, but the reason they look easy is because he is always there. He knows where to position himself even if he has two defenders around him. He never stops running and you hardly see him standing with his hands to his waist looking at his teammates.
